Trunk 
150 mm
in length in preserved specimens (
Fig. 4A
), 
300 mm
in living specimens. More than 60 filiform tentacles. Introvert with dispersed orange papillae (
Fig. 4C
) and reddish region with rectangular papillae (
Fig. 4D
). Trunk with light brown body wall (
Fig. 4E
). More than 100 rings of claw-shaped hooks (
Fig. 4G
). Twenty-six anastomosing longitudinal muscle bands (
Fig. 4H
). Two long, tiny and dark brown free nephridia occupying 40% of trunk, about 35% attached to body wall. Two pairs of retractor muscles; dorsal pair attached to five bands starting from second band after ventral nerve cord, ventral pair attached to nine bands (
Fig. 4B
). Multiple rectal caeca covering 90% of rectum (
Fig. 4F
). Spindle muscle attached posteriorly. Nephridiopore almost at same level of anus.
